    <stitle>HEAT VENTILATION AIR CONDITIONING (HVAC) SYSTEM - ProStar - REMOVE AND INSTALL - THERMISTORS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl160390802" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>THERMISTORS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>The AC thermistors
                        <emph type="boldundersc">CANNOT</emph>
                        be removed and installed without removing the refrigerant from the AC system. The procedures are
                        the same for either thermistor.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <note>
                    <para>Refer to
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1603925">Figure 25</hotlnk>
                        while performing the following Remove and Install procedures.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discharge A/C system. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16039_HL160390905.xml" xrefid="hl160390905">DISCHARGING THE SYSTEM</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="hl160390905"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect electrical connection to thermistor being removed.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unscrew thermistor from its fitting and cap open fitting.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1603925" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603925.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. A/C Thermistor Locations</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. EVAPORATOR OUTPUT THERMISTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. EVAPORATOR INPUT THERMISTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Ensure a new O-ring is installed on the new thermistor, and lubricate O-ring and threads
                    with mineral-based oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Screw thermistor into its fitting and tighten to 5.0 to 9.5 N.m&#160; (44.3 to 84.1
                    lbf-in).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The thermistor connector is not polarized. It may be connected in either orientation.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect electrical connection to replaced thermistor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Recharge A/C system. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16039_HL160390907.xml" xrefid="hl160390907">CHARGING THE AIR CONDITIONING
                        SYSTEM
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="hl160390907"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
